<body>
  <div class="lang-bar"><a href="/family-law/cross-border-assets">中文</a><a href="/en/family-law/cross-border-assets" class="active">EN</a></div>
  <Header />
  <div class="page">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/en/">Home</a> › Family Law › Cross-Border Asset Division</div>
    <h1>Cross-Border Asset Division</h1>
    <p class="lead">Holding both an Ontario and China bar licence, Miao He can directly investigate and handle assets held in China. This is a capability most Ontario lawyers simply do not have.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>THE DUAL-LICENCE ADVANTAGE</h2>
      <p>In high-net-worth divorces involving Chinese-Canadian families, assets are frequently held across both countries — real estate in China, company shares, family trusts, offshore accounts. Without a lawyer who understands both legal systems, significant assets can be missed or undervalued.</p>
      <p>Miao He is one of very few Ontario family lawyers who is also licensed in China, with the knowledge to trace, investigate, and argue for the proper division of these assets in Ontario proceedings.</p>
      <div class="highlight"><p>Verified outcome: $300,000+ in cross-border assets recovered for a client whose spouse concealed real estate and company shares held in China.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>WHAT WE HANDLE</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Real estate held in China — tracing, valuation, division</li>
        <li>Company shares and business interests in China</li>
        <li>Family trusts and offshore structures</li>
        <li>Hidden asset investigation</li>
        <li>Impact of Chinese divorce proceedings on Ontario equalization</li>
        <li>Choice of forum disputes — where to litigate</li>
        <li>CBV business valuation disputes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h2>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can an Ontario court divide property held in China?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Ontario courts can make orders regarding the equalization of net family property regardless of where assets are located. However, enforcing those orders in China requires a lawyer who understands both systems.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">My spouse is hiding assets in China. What can I do?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">We can use Ontario disclosure rules to compel your spouse to disclose overseas assets, and investigate through Chinese public records and corporate registries. Failure to disclose can result in serious cost consequences and adverse inferences at trial.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Does a divorce in China affect my Ontario proceedings?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">It can. The recognition of a Chinese divorce order in Ontario, and its impact on property division and support, is a complex area. We handle these cross-jurisdictional issues regularly.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card cta">
      <h2>Book a Consultation</h2>
      <a href="tel:6479306688" class="btn-primary">📞 647-930-6688</a>
      <a href="mailto:miao@miaohelaw.ca" class="btn-secondary">Email Us</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <Footer />
</body>
